Massive 10-meter high tidal waves powered by strong undersea earthquakes wiped out at least three of 12 affected villages on northwest coast of PNG's remote West Sepik province Friday night, leaving 6,000 homeless, the ABC News Radio reported Monday.
The Australian Associated Press (AAP) and the Australian Broadcasting Corporation (ABC) quoted missionaries or local PNG officials in the disaster-stricken areas as saying the death toll would surpass 3,000.
CANBERRA, July 20 (Xinhua)--The death toll of Papua New Guinea (PNG)'s tidal wave disaster may be more than 3,000, Australian media reported Monday.
